1
00:00:37,200 --> 00:00:38,467
<i> Please help my child!</i>

2
00:00:38,600 --> 00:00:39,700
<i> What happened to her?</i>

3
00:00:39,833 --> 00:00:41,967
<i>She had an asthma attack,
and she couldn't breathe.</i>

4
00:00:42,100 --> 00:00:43,900
<i>She had symptoms
of a heart murmur.</i>

5
00:00:44,033 --> 00:00:45,767
<i>The patient's heart
has a hole in it.</i>

6
00:00:45,900 --> 00:00:47,833
<i>Where are we going to get
00,000 pesos?</i>

7
00:00:47,967 --> 00:00:48,700
<i> I can try to go abroad.</i>

8
00:00:48,833 --> 00:00:50,067
<i> You're going to leave us?</i>

9
00:00:50,200 --> 00:00:51,800
<i>I won't be gone long.
Just two years.</i>

10
00:00:51,933 --> 00:00:54,833
<i>- Here, Hazel.
- Thank you.</i>

11
00:00:54,967 --> 00:00:55,967
<i> Manuel is so diligent.</i>

12
00:00:56,100 --> 00:00:56,733
<i> Who?</i>

13
00:00:56,867 --> 00:00:58,067
<i> Sir! Oh no!</i>

14
00:00:58,200 --> 00:00:59,367
<i>I think he threw up. I'm going
to clean up real quick.</i>

15
00:00:59,500 --> 00:01:01,533
<i> Yes, he did. Thank you.</i>

16
00:01:01,667 --> 00:01:03,167
<i> Go, lower it a bit.</i>

17
00:01:03,300 --> 00:01:04,100
<i> Hazel!</i>

18
00:01:04,233 --> 00:01:05,700
<i> Hazel!</i>

19
00:01:05,833 --> 00:01:07,067
<i> Manuel!</i>

20
00:01:07,200 --> 00:01:11,233
<i>So the damsel in distress has
finally met her prince charming!</i>

21
00:01:11,400 --> 00:01:13,200
<i> You're lucky to have Charles.</i>

22
00:01:13,333 --> 00:01:14,433
<i> He seems to love you.</i>

23
00:01:14,567 --> 00:01:17,633
<i>Don't worry, you'll find
someone like him, too.</i>

24
00:01:17,767 --> 00:01:19,233
<i> I think I found someone.</i>

25
00:01:19,367 --> 00:01:20,633
<i> Or...</i>

26
00:01:20,767 --> 00:01:24,233
<i>more on someone to help me
raise my baby.</i>

27
00:01:25,200 --> 00:01:26,400
I didn't know they had
a compound like this

28
00:01:26,533 --> 00:01:28,300
in Saudi Arabia.

29
00:01:28,433 --> 00:01:29,500
Yes,

30
00:01:29,633 --> 00:01:32,800
the residents
are mostly Westerners.

31
00:01:32,933 --> 00:01:36,200
Yes, mostly white people,
Canadians, and British.

32
00:01:36,333 --> 00:01:37,933
They reside here
with their family.

33
00:01:38,967 --> 00:01:43,467
They have more freedom here,
than the rest.

34
00:01:43,633 --> 00:01:47,267
You're so right.
Here we can drink and eat pork.

35
00:01:47,400 --> 00:01:50,567
Women and men can rent
a place together.

36
00:01:50,700 --> 00:01:53,500
The police won't bother us.

37
00:01:53,633 --> 00:01:55,600
The police?

38
00:01:55,733 --> 00:01:58,633
Yes, the religious
police officers.

39
00:01:58,767 --> 00:02:01,633
Those bearded men.

40
00:02:01,767 --> 00:02:03,867
Those guys who wore pants
that were a bit short.

41
00:02:04,000 --> 00:02:06,100
They're patrolling outside.

42
00:02:06,233 --> 00:02:08,467
- That's them. Right.
- Thank you.

43
00:02:08,600 --> 00:02:12,200
They don't come
into this compound.

44
00:02:12,333 --> 00:02:16,333
They respect Westerners
more than us, Asians.

45
00:02:16,500 --> 00:02:20,200
So they don't bother
the white people here.

46
00:02:21,800 --> 00:02:22,600
Wait a minute.

47
00:02:22,733 --> 00:02:24,000
Why are we talking about them?

48
00:02:24,133 --> 00:02:26,733
Didn't we come here to party?

49
00:02:26,867 --> 00:02:30,733
So what are we waiting for?
Should we eat now, or...

50
00:02:30,867 --> 00:02:33,500
wait, let's take
a picture first.

51
00:02:33,633 --> 00:02:36,067
Before we start
eating and drinking,

52
00:02:36,200 --> 00:02:37,367
we should wait for Charles.

53
00:02:37,500 --> 00:02:39,033
Oh, yeah. How long will it take
for him to get here?

54
00:02:39,167 --> 00:02:41,400
I don't drink.

55
00:02:41,533 --> 00:02:42,933
Okay, let's all take
a picture first.

56
00:02:43,067 --> 00:02:44,833
- Guys! Let's take a picture.
- Drink a little!

57
00:02:44,967 --> 00:02:46,467
Come on, let's take a picture
before Charles gets here.

58
00:02:46,600 --> 00:02:49,333
- Come on. You won't get drunk.
- Where's my husband?

59
00:02:49,500 --> 00:02:51,400
- Let's take a picture, come on.
- Okay, let's go.

60
00:02:51,533 --> 00:02:52,700
- Okay, let's take a picture.
- Yes, picture.

61
00:02:52,833 --> 00:02:54,700
- Ready?
- Charles isn't here yet.

62
00:02:54,833 --> 00:02:56,000
Okay.

63
00:02:56,133 --> 00:02:57,100
Come on!

64
00:02:57,233 --> 00:02:58,133
- Ready?
- Say cheese!

65
00:02:58,267 --> 00:03:03,067
- Cheese.
- Cheese.

66
00:03:03,200 --> 00:03:05,200
That's delicious,
I thought you wanted some cake?

67
00:03:05,333 --> 00:03:07,167
Maybe later.
I'll finish this for now.

68
00:03:07,300 --> 00:03:09,133
That's for dessert.

69
00:03:09,267 --> 00:03:10,200
Thanks for coming, guys.

70
00:03:10,333 --> 00:03:12,933
It's not easy to work
here in Saudi Arabia.

71
00:03:13,067 --> 00:03:17,633
Of course, we all do
everything for our family.

72
00:03:17,767 --> 00:03:20,867
My mom is old and sickly,

73
00:03:21,033 --> 00:03:27,667
so when my dad died, I became
the breadwinner of the family.

74
00:03:27,800 --> 00:03:31,133
I pay for my
siblings' education.

75
00:03:31,267 --> 00:03:34,433
How about you?
Are you the breadwinner too?

76
00:03:34,567 --> 00:03:36,800
My wife helps out too.

77
00:03:36,933 --> 00:03:38,700
I'm lucky to have Felma.

78
00:03:38,833 --> 00:03:39,933
She's hardworking.

79
00:03:40,067 --> 00:03:42,933
She wakes up very early in
the morning to go to the market.

80
00:03:43,067 --> 00:03:45,700
To buy stuff for her
homemade longganisa.

81
00:03:45,833 --> 00:03:48,367
Then she sells all of them.

82
00:03:48,500 --> 00:03:52,267
Then she takes care of our
children once she gets home.

83
00:03:52,400 --> 00:03:54,600
That's why I'm working hard.

84
00:03:54,767 --> 00:03:58,100
So that I have some savings when
it's time to come home.

85
00:03:58,233 --> 00:04:02,600
So my wife can get a break.

86
00:04:02,733 --> 00:04:04,167
I miss my wife.

87
00:04:06,033 --> 00:04:08,033
You love her so much, don't you?

88
00:04:08,167 --> 00:04:09,633
Of course.

89
00:04:09,767 --> 00:04:13,067
When you love someone, you
will give them everything.

90
00:04:13,200 --> 00:04:15,667
And you take your
relationship seriously.

91
00:04:17,367 --> 00:04:18,633
Do you have any siblings?

92
00:04:20,433 --> 00:04:22,600
No, I have a son, though.

93
00:04:25,167 --> 00:04:26,700
Here, look.

94
00:04:26,833 --> 00:04:28,167
This is my family.

95
00:04:30,533 --> 00:04:32,333
That's my oldest son.

96
00:04:32,467 --> 00:04:35,367
His name is Jeffrey.
He's good at playing basketball.

97
00:04:35,500 --> 00:04:37,567
Of course, I'm the one
who taught him.

98
00:04:37,700 --> 00:04:41,200
Then this one is Andrea.
She's a good student.

99
00:04:41,333 --> 00:04:44,300
She likes to draw.

100
00:04:44,433 --> 00:04:45,433
And this one is Coleen.

101
00:04:45,567 --> 00:04:48,067
- She's my baby.
- Oh, cute!

102
00:04:48,200 --> 00:04:50,200
Who does she look like?

103
00:04:50,333 --> 00:04:51,800
I think she's a mix
between you and your wife.

104
00:04:51,933 --> 00:04:54,800
But you have a good lineage.

105
00:04:55,933 --> 00:04:58,200
Music is on, guys.

106
00:04:58,333 --> 00:04:59,833
Come on, let's dance?

107
00:04:59,967 --> 00:05:03,267
- Let's dance!
- Come on, let's join them.

108
00:05:03,433 --> 00:05:05,267
- Come on, let's go.
- I don't know how to dance.

109
00:05:05,400 --> 00:05:07,533
Come on, it's easy.

110
00:05:07,667 --> 00:05:09,167
You go ahead,
I'll just watch you guys.

111
00:05:09,300 --> 00:05:11,700
Come on, just move like Abel.

112
00:05:11,833 --> 00:05:14,233
Look at him. Abel,
teach your friend how to dance.

113
00:05:14,367 --> 00:05:16,333
Just like this.

114
00:05:16,467 --> 00:05:18,267
Like this.

115
00:05:18,400 --> 00:05:21,667
- A cool dance move, right?
- That's right!

116
00:05:25,367 --> 00:05:27,333
Like this?

117
00:05:27,467 --> 00:05:30,133
You see, you're good at dancing.

118
00:05:30,267 --> 00:05:31,267
You're acting like you
don't know how to dance.

119
00:05:31,400 --> 00:05:36,100
- No, I'm so stiff.
- You're very cool with it.

120
00:05:36,267 --> 00:05:38,167
But you know what, you should...

121
00:05:38,300 --> 00:05:39,533
Hey! Give us some!

122
00:05:39,667 --> 00:05:42,167
- There's nothing left for us.
- Sorry.

123
00:05:42,300 --> 00:05:43,533
- Here you go.
- Yes, we'll have that.

124
00:05:43,667 --> 00:05:45,067
- I don't drink.
- What are you talking about?

125
00:05:45,200 --> 00:05:46,833
Just a little.

126
00:05:46,967 --> 00:05:48,833
Here. Some more,
some more, please.

127
00:05:48,967 --> 00:05:50,600
- More?
- Yes.

128
00:05:50,733 --> 00:05:52,267
- Look at that. That's fine.
- More.

129
00:05:52,400 --> 00:05:53,467
Enough, enough.

130
00:05:53,600 --> 00:05:55,633
Just a little.

131
00:05:55,767 --> 00:05:57,067
Cheers!

132
00:05:57,200 --> 00:05:58,767
Come on. This is only a little.

133
00:05:58,900 --> 00:05:59,467
Cheers.

134
00:05:59,600 --> 00:06:00,800
Okay, go on.

135
00:06:00,933 --> 00:06:02,167
- I'm getting tipsy already.
- Come on.

136
00:06:02,300 --> 00:06:05,000
Look at me, I don't
drink much either.

137
00:06:10,500 --> 00:06:12,933
My gosh, that's nothing.

138
00:06:13,067 --> 00:06:15,767
- Drink one more. Here.
- No more.

139
00:06:19,400 --> 00:06:22,000
Are you okay?
You're fine, right?

140
00:06:22,133 --> 00:06:22,933
Are you dizzy?

141
00:06:23,067 --> 00:06:24,533
- I am.
- Here, you can hold on to me.

142
00:06:24,667 --> 00:06:25,800
So you won't fall.

143
00:06:25,933 --> 00:06:27,133
Hold on to me, like this.

144
00:06:27,267 --> 00:06:28,433
- Okay?
- Okay.

145
00:06:28,567 --> 00:06:31,367
We'll drink again?
That doesn't even taste good.

146
00:07:06,433 --> 00:07:10,300
<i>I want you to be all
better when I get home.</i>

147
00:07:10,433 --> 00:07:13,667
<i>I will bring you to
the beach, I promise.</i>

148
00:07:13,800 --> 00:07:16,333
<i>You can run around at the beach
as much as you want.</i>

149
00:07:17,433 --> 00:07:19,667
<i> I miss you so much.</i>

150
00:07:19,800 --> 00:07:20,933
<i> I love you.</i>

151
00:07:29,133 --> 00:07:30,367
Dear.

152
00:07:32,900 --> 00:07:34,133
Dear.

153
00:07:34,267 --> 00:07:35,833
Hey, why are you still up?

154
00:07:41,733 --> 00:07:43,833
I forgot my...

155
00:07:45,500 --> 00:07:47,067
inhaler outside.

156
00:07:48,733 --> 00:07:50,833
Your inhaler, wait here.

157
00:08:03,600 --> 00:08:04,600
Andrea.

158
00:08:05,667 --> 00:08:06,700
Andrea!

159
00:08:07,233 --> 00:08:09,367
Andrea! Sweetie!

160
00:08:09,500 --> 00:08:11,200
Sweetie, Andrea!

161
00:08:11,333 --> 00:08:13,067
Dear!

162
00:08:13,200 --> 00:08:14,300
Jeffrey!

163
00:08:14,433 --> 00:08:15,300
Jeffrey!

164
00:08:15,433 --> 00:08:17,767
- Dear.
- Andrea!

165
00:08:17,900 --> 00:08:18,800
Andrea!

166
00:08:18,933 --> 00:08:21,133
Dear! Wake up, Andrea!

167
00:08:21,300 --> 00:08:22,833
Andrea!

168
00:08:22,967 --> 00:08:25,000
Our neighbors!

169
00:08:28,033 --> 00:08:31,400
Neighbors! Help us, please!

170
00:08:35,633 --> 00:08:37,933
Ma'am, can we talk for awhile?

171
00:08:41,700 --> 00:08:43,167
My dear...

172
00:08:43,300 --> 00:08:44,500
Sweetie,

173
00:08:44,633 --> 00:08:46,733
I'm just going to talk
to your doctor, okay?

174
00:08:54,400 --> 00:08:56,767
- Yes, doctor?
- Mrs. Cruz.

175
00:08:56,933 --> 00:08:59,167
Based on our initial test,

176
00:08:59,300 --> 00:09:01,867
there's a possibility

177
00:09:02,000 --> 00:09:05,067
that your daughter
had pulmonary hypertension.

178
00:09:06,833 --> 00:09:08,133
What is that?

179
00:09:08,267 --> 00:09:10,067
Her lungs were overloaded
with blood

180
00:09:10,200 --> 00:09:12,433
because of the hole
in her heart.

181
00:09:12,567 --> 00:09:15,200
She needs to get
surgery immediately.

182
00:09:15,333 --> 00:09:16,300
What?

183
00:09:19,500 --> 00:09:24,467
We don't know where we can
get that amount of money.

184
00:09:24,600 --> 00:09:27,800
Perhaps you have some relatives
who can help,

185
00:09:27,967 --> 00:09:29,300
or maybe a charity.

186
00:09:29,433 --> 00:09:33,300
You need to make a decision
as soon as possible.

187
00:09:36,200 --> 00:09:37,500
Excuse me.

188
00:10:22,133 --> 00:10:23,100
Manuel...

189
00:10:24,900 --> 00:10:26,533
answer the phone.

190
00:10:32,767 --> 00:10:35,300
Why aren't you answering
the phone?

191
00:10:44,733 --> 00:10:46,900
Manuel, answer the phone.

192
00:10:54,700 --> 00:10:57,233
Manuel, answer the phone.

193
00:10:57,367 --> 00:10:59,400
Manuel, answer the phone.

194
00:11:38,833 --> 00:11:40,033
What happened?

195
00:11:41,767 --> 00:11:43,033
You have the guts to ask.

196
00:11:44,400 --> 00:11:46,433
You got too drunk last night.

197
00:11:46,567 --> 00:11:48,267
And you kissed me.

198
00:11:49,933 --> 00:11:52,067
I didn't want this to happen,
but...

199
00:11:52,200 --> 00:11:53,600
But I couldn't do anything.

200
00:11:55,533 --> 00:11:56,867
I was drunk, too.

201
00:12:02,433 --> 00:12:05,000
<i>- Here.
- I don't drink anymore.</i>

202
00:12:05,133 --> 00:12:07,333
<i> Come on, drink a little.</i>

203
00:12:07,467 --> 00:12:08,333
<i> Are you okay?</i>

204
00:12:08,467 --> 00:12:09,633
<i> I'm getting tipsy.</i>

205
00:12:09,767 --> 00:12:13,800
<i>Come on, you only
had a little drink.</i>

206
00:12:13,933 --> 00:12:15,100
Hazel, forgive me.

207
00:12:15,267 --> 00:12:19,600
You know that I respect you.
And I have a family back home.

208
00:12:19,733 --> 00:12:20,967
I'm sorry.

209
00:12:21,100 --> 00:12:22,933
But something happened
between us.

210
00:12:23,067 --> 00:12:24,567
Manuel.

211
00:12:24,700 --> 00:12:26,067
You did this to me.

212
00:12:26,200 --> 00:12:28,533
- Where are you going?
- I need to go.

213
00:12:28,667 --> 00:12:29,633
Manuel!

214
00:12:49,433 --> 00:12:51,400
What took you so long?

215
00:12:51,533 --> 00:12:53,467
Your wife's been trying to call!

216
00:12:53,600 --> 00:12:54,733
Paz has been nagging me, too.

217
00:12:54,867 --> 00:12:56,467
She said they couldn't
reach you.

218
00:12:56,600 --> 00:12:57,900
What happened?

219
00:12:59,033 --> 00:13:00,667
Why did Felma call?

220
00:13:02,200 --> 00:13:03,933
It's about Andrea.

221
00:13:13,067 --> 00:13:14,867
Manuel?

222
00:13:15,000 --> 00:13:16,367
Hello, Love.

223
00:13:16,500 --> 00:13:18,233
Finally, Manuel,

224
00:13:18,367 --> 00:13:19,867
what happened?

225
00:13:20,000 --> 00:13:23,567
Wait, why aren't you
answering my calls?

226
00:13:23,733 --> 00:13:25,600
Are you okay?

227
00:13:25,733 --> 00:13:27,567
I'm sorry.

228
00:13:27,700 --> 00:13:29,400
What happened to Andrea?
How is she?

229
00:13:29,533 --> 00:13:31,933
She had another attack
last night.

230
00:13:32,067 --> 00:13:34,167
That's why I brought her here
to the hospital.

231
00:13:34,300 --> 00:13:39,500
Doctor Gallardo told me
that her heart is failing.

232
00:13:39,633 --> 00:13:42,800
She needed to get
surgery immediately.

233
00:13:54,500 --> 00:13:56,333
My God, is this what you mean

234
00:13:56,467 --> 00:13:58,733
when you said you found someone
to help you raise your baby?

235
00:13:58,867 --> 00:14:01,300
So, you're going to make
Manuel accountable for it?

236
00:14:02,533 --> 00:14:05,600
How are you going to make him
believe that it's his baby?

237
00:14:05,733 --> 00:14:07,400
It's easy.

238
00:14:07,533 --> 00:14:09,200
I'm just going to wait
a couple more weeks.

239
00:14:10,333 --> 00:14:12,567
I think my pregnancy
won't be showing by then.

240
00:14:14,233 --> 00:14:18,067
He doesn't know that
I'm already two months pregnant.

241
00:14:20,733 --> 00:14:23,600
Anyway, how is his performance?

242
00:14:23,733 --> 00:14:25,367
Is he good in bed?

243
00:14:29,000 --> 00:14:30,100
Come on!

244
00:14:30,233 --> 00:14:32,367
You make me laugh.

245
00:14:35,133 --> 00:14:37,300
Poor Manuel.

246
00:14:37,433 --> 00:14:39,633
You got him in this trouble.

247
00:14:39,767 --> 00:14:41,700
He's not even your type.

248
00:14:42,600 --> 00:14:45,467
Didn't you say you don't like
him because of his occupation?

249
00:14:47,367 --> 00:14:48,967
Didn't you tell me how kind
he is?

250
00:14:50,233 --> 00:14:56,867
He's hardworking, and he's
a decent person, unlike Jojo.

251
00:14:57,700 --> 00:15:00,800
And I saw how much
he loves his family.

252
00:15:00,933 --> 00:15:05,333
I think he would love my baby,
too.

253
00:15:07,600 --> 00:15:08,767
Friend,

254
00:15:08,900 --> 00:15:13,000
if you think that
this would work, then go ahead.

255
00:15:13,133 --> 00:15:17,433
As long as you're safe
and you won't go to jail.

256
00:15:17,567 --> 00:15:20,633
And you won't get deported.

257
00:15:28,067 --> 00:15:30,000
What time will the seminar
start?

258
00:15:30,133 --> 00:15:34,967
Nine in the morning. We still
have time to check our patients.

259
00:15:41,233 --> 00:15:43,767
Bro, she needs to get a heart
surgery, or else,

260
00:15:43,900 --> 00:15:47,033
her lungs will be affected.

261
00:15:47,167 --> 00:15:49,133
If that happens,

262
00:15:50,367 --> 00:15:52,700
my child might not make it.

263
00:15:54,800 --> 00:15:56,900
She could die.

264
00:15:58,833 --> 00:16:03,367
Bro, I can't lose my child.

265
00:16:03,500 --> 00:16:05,333
You're not gonna lose her.

266
00:16:05,467 --> 00:16:07,333
Bro, she will be okay.

267
00:16:07,467 --> 00:16:10,767
We'll all chip in. We'll get the
money together.

268
00:16:10,933 --> 00:16:16,700
Paz knows of some charity that
could help.

269
00:16:16,833 --> 00:16:19,100
I feel ashamed.

270
00:16:19,233 --> 00:16:21,300
I should be doing something.

271
00:16:21,433 --> 00:16:24,267
I should be with my family.

272
00:16:24,400 --> 00:16:25,833
But look where I am.

273
00:16:25,967 --> 00:16:28,300
I was partying while
my daughter was in the hospital.

274
00:16:28,433 --> 00:16:30,700
You didn't do anything wrong.

275
00:16:30,833 --> 00:16:32,500
You didn't know she's in
the hospital.

276
00:16:32,633 --> 00:16:35,067
It's just wrong timing.

277
00:16:36,500 --> 00:16:38,667
What happened?

278
00:16:39,233 --> 00:16:41,167
We were looking all over
for you.

279
00:16:41,300 --> 00:16:43,633
So we could all sober
up together.

280
00:16:43,800 --> 00:16:45,167
But we couldn't find you.

281
00:16:45,867 --> 00:16:47,567
We couldn't find Hazel, either.

282
00:16:49,767 --> 00:16:52,633
My gosh, we didn't leave
till dawn.

283
00:16:52,767 --> 00:16:55,600
I thought you already went
back to our apartment.

284
00:16:57,700 --> 00:16:58,567
Bro,

285
00:16:59,800 --> 00:17:01,500
something happened
between you and Hazel, right?

286
00:17:06,333 --> 00:17:08,133
I worry about that, too.

287
00:17:09,833 --> 00:17:12,233
I didn't mean to do it.

288
00:17:14,800 --> 00:17:17,867
I'm in big trouble
if Felma finds out.

289
00:17:18,000 --> 00:17:20,167
What do you mean?

290
00:17:20,300 --> 00:17:22,100
Why would you tell her?

291
00:17:22,233 --> 00:17:23,533
What are you thinking?

292
00:17:23,667 --> 00:17:26,200
Bro, your wife wouldn't get hurt

293
00:17:26,333 --> 00:17:27,700
as long as she doesn't
know anything.

294
00:17:27,833 --> 00:17:31,733
Look at me. Paz and I have no
problem because I'm discreet.

295
00:17:31,867 --> 00:17:33,733
We're not the same!

296
00:17:33,867 --> 00:17:37,133
And I didn't mean to do it.
And it won't happen again.

297
00:17:38,433 --> 00:17:41,667
Can we change the subject? Where
can we get the money I need?

298
00:17:42,300 --> 00:17:46,333
We can't get a loan from
the bank. It's impossible.

299
00:17:46,467 --> 00:17:47,967
They will look at our paycheck,

300
00:17:48,100 --> 00:17:50,300
and it's too small compared
to others.

301
00:17:57,033 --> 00:17:59,400
What if I borrow from
the agency?

302
00:18:12,467 --> 00:18:15,300
She still gets tired easily.

303
00:18:17,333 --> 00:18:20,067
I hope we can gather the money
for her surgery.

304
00:18:20,200 --> 00:18:23,933
What did Manuel say? When will
he send you money?

305
00:18:24,100 --> 00:18:27,467
He tried to borrow money
from his agency but...

306
00:18:29,133 --> 00:18:30,633
They don't give advance payment.

307
00:18:35,467 --> 00:18:37,167
Sis, I'm worried...

308
00:18:38,633 --> 00:18:40,633
I'm worried that she might...

309
00:18:40,767 --> 00:18:42,933
- She might not make it...
- Sis, si.

310
00:18:43,067 --> 00:18:44,733
- till the surgery.
- Sis, stop.

311
00:18:44,867 --> 00:18:48,467
Sis, don't talk like that.

312
00:18:48,600 --> 00:18:51,367
God will not forsake her.

313
00:18:51,500 --> 00:18:53,300
God loves her.

314
00:18:53,433 --> 00:18:57,533
And we're doing everything
we can.

315
00:18:57,700 --> 00:19:00,733
I'm working on her paperwork,
all the requirements

316
00:19:00,867 --> 00:19:03,000
to get help from charity.

317
00:19:03,133 --> 00:19:06,333
Hold on, okay. Have faith.

318
00:19:18,067 --> 00:19:21,533
Here, please accept our little
help for your family.

319
00:19:21,667 --> 00:19:23,267
Thank you so much.

320
00:19:23,400 --> 00:19:25,133
For your daughter.

321
00:19:25,267 --> 00:19:26,000
Thank you.

322
00:19:27,933 --> 00:19:29,733
Take care of your daughter.

323
00:19:29,900 --> 00:19:31,200
Thank you.

324
00:19:32,867 --> 00:19:35,767
I hope this can help
your family.

325
00:19:36,667 --> 00:19:37,767
Thank you.

326
00:19:40,433 --> 00:19:42,200
Thank you so much.

327
00:19:42,333 --> 00:19:45,433
This is a big help for
my daughters' surgery.

328
00:19:45,567 --> 00:19:47,967
I'm sorry for the trouble.

329
00:19:48,100 --> 00:19:49,833
Don't mention it. It's nothing.

330
00:19:49,967 --> 00:19:51,767
We're family here.

331
00:19:51,900 --> 00:19:55,200
Who else would help each other
but us, fellow countrymen?

332
00:19:55,333 --> 00:19:58,700
Don't worry. I'll talk to the
doctors from another unit.

333
00:19:58,833 --> 00:20:00,600
They will help out, too.

334
00:20:00,733 --> 00:20:02,033
Thank you so much.

335
00:20:02,200 --> 00:20:04,200
I have to go.

336
00:20:09,333 --> 00:20:11,567
Hey, what's that?

337
00:20:12,933 --> 00:20:14,433
What's going on?

338
00:20:16,433 --> 00:20:18,200
It's for his daughter.

339
00:20:18,333 --> 00:20:20,767
She needs to get surgery.

340
00:20:26,600 --> 00:20:27,767
- Here.
- No, thank you.

341
00:20:27,900 --> 00:20:30,067
No, Hazel. It's fine.

342
00:20:31,667 --> 00:20:33,333
I want to help.

343
00:20:37,500 --> 00:20:39,333
Okay, we have to go.

344
00:20:54,433 --> 00:20:55,433
Hello?

345
00:20:58,333 --> 00:20:59,367
Who is this?

346
00:21:05,400 --> 00:21:07,500
Why do you have
my husband's phone?

347
00:21:08,667 --> 00:21:11,700
- Where's Manuel?
- He left his phone.

348
00:21:11,833 --> 00:21:13,033
But he was here earlier.

349
00:21:13,167 --> 00:21:15,433
He's soliciting money
for your daughter.

350
00:21:15,567 --> 00:21:17,267
<i> How is she?</i>

351
00:21:18,800 --> 00:21:20,267
She's still not doing so well.

352
00:21:21,100 --> 00:21:23,000
<i> What is your name?</i>

353
00:21:25,300 --> 00:21:28,133
Hello? Hello?

354
00:21:38,333 --> 00:21:39,800
Ouch!

355
00:21:40,733 --> 00:21:43,267
Let go of me! What are
you doing?

356
00:21:43,433 --> 00:21:45,400
Don't you ever talk to my wife,
do you understand?

357
00:21:45,533 --> 00:21:46,433
Why?

358
00:21:46,567 --> 00:21:47,500
Are you scared that she might
find out

359
00:21:47,633 --> 00:21:49,300
what happened between us?

360
00:21:49,433 --> 00:21:51,033
There's nothing for her
to find out!

361
00:21:51,167 --> 00:21:53,367
It only happened once! And it
won't happen again!

362
00:21:53,500 --> 00:21:55,600
So can you please forget
about that night!

363
00:22:04,733 --> 00:22:06,200
Are you okay?

364
00:22:10,000 --> 00:22:11,100
Manuel...

365
00:22:13,533 --> 00:22:15,133
I'm pregnant.

366
00:22:19,467 --> 00:22:20,967
You got me pregnant.

367
00:22:24,900 --> 00:22:26,033
Manuel...

368
00:22:27,567 --> 00:22:29,200
did you hear what I said?

369
00:22:29,867 --> 00:22:33,433
I said, you got me pregnant.

370
00:22:33,567 --> 00:22:35,067
You're the father.

371
00:22:35,200 --> 00:22:37,033
That's not possible!

372
00:22:37,167 --> 00:22:39,133
That child is not mine!

373
00:22:42,100 --> 00:22:43,433
What do you think of me?

374
00:22:44,100 --> 00:22:46,467
Do you think I hook up
with anyone?

375
00:22:47,700 --> 00:22:49,167
It only happened once!

376
00:22:49,333 --> 00:22:52,033
That's enough to get
a woman pregnant!

377
00:22:52,167 --> 00:22:54,500
It's too early to tell!

378
00:22:54,633 --> 00:22:56,667
I have a regular period.

379
00:22:57,600 --> 00:23:01,033
When I missed my period,
I took a pregnancy test.

380
00:23:02,100 --> 00:23:03,433
It turned out positive.

381
00:23:04,667 --> 00:23:06,133
I'm pregnant.

382
00:23:16,233 --> 00:23:19,633
I will support the child. I will
help you. I will do that.

383
00:23:21,433 --> 00:23:23,900
That's not what I need, Manuel.

384
00:23:25,533 --> 00:23:27,533
We're in Saudi Arabia.

385
00:23:27,667 --> 00:23:29,300
They have a different law.

386
00:23:31,967 --> 00:23:38,700
It's a crime for an unmarried
person to get pregnant here.

387
00:23:42,767 --> 00:23:44,167
You want me to marry you?

388
00:23:45,167 --> 00:23:46,133
Yes.

389
00:23:49,100 --> 00:23:53,233
Because once they see me
pregnant without a husband,

390
00:23:53,367 --> 00:23:56,000
they will punish me.

391
00:23:58,133 --> 00:23:59,500
And I will get you involved.

392
00:24:00,500 --> 00:24:03,033
Because you committed
premarital sex,

393
00:24:03,167 --> 00:24:05,300
they will punish you too.

394
00:24:06,300 --> 00:24:08,467
We will both get punished.

395
00:24:09,100 --> 00:24:11,000
Both of us will get imprisoned.

396
00:24:38,400 --> 00:24:41,733
They won't just
face imprisonment.

397
00:24:41,867 --> 00:24:46,200
You will also be flogged
and have to pay a big penalty.

398
00:24:49,033 --> 00:24:53,467
But Sir, I didn't mean that to
happen.

399
00:24:53,600 --> 00:24:56,167
It doesn't matter if you ment it
to happen or not.

400
00:24:56,300 --> 00:24:59,500
The point is you committed
premarital sex.

401
00:24:59,633 --> 00:25:01,033
It's a serious crime here.

402
00:25:04,700 --> 00:25:07,733
Can they not push through
with the wedding?

403
00:25:07,867 --> 00:25:11,333
Maybe, there are other ways,
attorney?

404
00:25:11,467 --> 00:25:16,367
If I go back to the Philippines,
can they still sue me?

405
00:25:16,500 --> 00:25:17,567
No, they can't.

406
00:25:17,700 --> 00:25:19,300
There's no extradition treaty

407
00:25:19,433 --> 00:25:21,100
between the Philippines and
Saudi Arabia.

408
00:25:21,233 --> 00:25:23,300
Once you're in the Philippines,

409
00:25:23,433 --> 00:25:25,700
they can't hold you
accountable anymore.

410
00:25:25,833 --> 00:25:27,767
They can't imprison you.

411
00:25:37,000 --> 00:25:39,333
Here, your emergency leave
is approved, Manuel.

412
00:25:39,733 --> 00:25:40,767
Thank you, Ma'am.

413
00:25:41,267 --> 00:25:42,867
I can go home now.

414
00:25:43,000 --> 00:25:44,600
If this isn't emergency leave,

415
00:25:44,733 --> 00:25:47,633
the agency will pay
for your plane ticket.

416
00:25:48,400 --> 00:25:50,433
It's okay. I will get my plane
ticket.

417
00:25:50,567 --> 00:25:54,400
We will give you your passport
the day of your departure.

418
00:25:54,533 --> 00:25:57,500
Our staff will meet you
at the airport.

419
00:25:57,633 --> 00:25:59,733
And then we'll issue your
re-entry visa

420
00:25:59,867 --> 00:26:01,933
on your way back here.

421
00:26:04,733 --> 00:26:07,133
You will come back here, right?

422
00:26:08,300 --> 00:26:09,367
Yes, Ma'am.

423
00:26:10,933 --> 00:26:11,533
Good.

424
00:26:15,933 --> 00:26:20,567
Doctor Galliardo is coordinating
with Andrea's heart surgeon.

425
00:26:20,700 --> 00:26:22,567
<i>Love, Andrea needs to get
admitted to the hospital.</i>

426
00:26:22,700 --> 00:26:27,167
They need to do a lot
of preparation for the surgery.

427
00:26:27,300 --> 00:26:33,267
<i>We got some money from charity,
but it's not enough.</i>

428
00:26:33,400 --> 00:26:34,767
<i> Don't worry, Love.</i>

429
00:26:34,900 --> 00:26:39,267
<i>The doctors and my co-workers
here gave us some money.</i>

430
00:26:39,400 --> 00:26:41,500
And I'm gonna try to ask
my supervisor

431
00:26:41,633 --> 00:26:43,000
if they can lend me some money.

432
00:26:43,533 --> 00:26:45,333
If ever the money
will not be enough,

433
00:26:45,467 --> 00:26:49,033
I will find a solution to that
when I come back home.

434
00:26:49,167 --> 00:26:50,200
<i> You're coming home?</i>

435
00:26:52,133 --> 00:26:54,767
<i>Yes, Love. I already got
a ticket.</i>

436
00:26:54,900 --> 00:26:57,400
<i> Isn't that too sudden?</i>

437
00:26:57,533 --> 00:27:00,633
<i>What's going on?
Is there a problem?</i>

438
00:27:00,767 --> 00:27:01,733
Why?

439
00:27:01,867 --> 00:27:04,133
Don't you want me to come home?

440
00:27:04,267 --> 00:27:08,933
Of course, I do.
I'm just wondering.

441
00:27:09,767 --> 00:27:11,867
I'll explain when I get there.

442
00:27:13,867 --> 00:27:15,033
I have to go.

443
00:27:20,700 --> 00:27:23,700
<i>I couldn't wait to see you
and our kids.</i>

444
00:27:24,933 --> 00:27:26,367
Me too, Love.

445
00:27:26,500 --> 00:27:30,633
You know how much I need
you here.

446
00:27:50,233 --> 00:27:52,633
Did you really think you
could run away from me?

447
00:27:56,133 --> 00:28:03,200
I will tell those police
that you raped me!

448
00:28:03,333 --> 00:28:05,900
Did you really think you
won't get imprisoned?

449
00:28:06,033 --> 00:28:08,933
You're the only one who will go
to jail cause I'm a victim.

450
00:28:09,067 --> 00:28:10,500
You won't just get imprisoned.

451
00:28:10,633 --> 00:28:12,667
You might get beheaded, too.

452
00:28:15,133 --> 00:28:16,500
<i> Hello, Love.</i>

453
00:28:16,633 --> 00:28:18,100
Where have you been?

454
00:28:18,233 --> 00:28:19,233
We've been trying to call you.

455
00:28:19,367 --> 00:28:21,300
But you're not answering
your phone.

456
00:28:21,433 --> 00:28:25,033
I had a problem with
my employer.

457
00:28:25,200 --> 00:28:27,700
You can't return
to the Philippines

458
00:28:27,833 --> 00:28:29,967
until you pay off your debt.

459
00:28:30,100 --> 00:28:33,333
You know that I love you
so much, right?

460
00:28:34,233 --> 00:28:35,767
<i> Why are you talking like that?</i>

461
00:28:36,400 --> 00:28:38,700
I just want to make sure
that you know

462
00:28:38,833 --> 00:28:39,900
how much I love you.

463
00:28:40,033 --> 00:28:42,433
<i> I couldn't ask for more.</i>

464
00:28:42,567 --> 00:28:47,067
<i>You're a good husband,
a good father.</i>

465
00:28:47,200 --> 00:28:50,600
<i>Thank you so much for all
your sacrifices for our family.</i>

466
00:28:50,733 --> 00:28:53,600
Under the law of
the Republic of the Philippines,

467
00:28:53,733 --> 00:28:59,600
I ask you, Manuel Cruz, if you
freely and voluntarily consent

468
00:28:59,767 --> 00:29:03,467
to be united in marriage
to Hazel Capistrano.
